TITLE: New Mexico governor warns about 'serious' weekend fire weather
SUMMARY: New Mexico's governor warned residents on Friday ahead of what is expected to be a historic and dangerous weekend for fire weather. Gov. Michelle Lujan Grisham encouraged people still in mandatory evacuation areas to leave as soon as possible.

TITLE: West Virginia flooding kills 1, governor declares State of Preparedness
SUMMARY: West Virginia streets flooded Friday after several inches of heavy rain fell in and around the Ohio River community. Fox Weather reported that one person was killed and several others were rescued in the event.

TITLE: Alabama prison fugitives Casey White, Vicky White 'would be fools to leave the country:' longtime USMS exec
SUMMARY: Investigators are likely turning Vicky White’s "world upside down" as they intensify their manhunt for the fugitive corrections officer and the prison escapee, Casey Cole White, who disappeared from an Alabama facility more than a week ago, says longtime U.S. Marshal Service commander Lenny DePaul.

TITLE: New York man sentenced to 27 years to life after killing, dismembering woman then putting her remains in bags
SUMMARY: A jury in New York found Daquan Wheeler guilty of killing and dismembering a woman in 2018, and sentenced him to 27 years to life in prison during a hearing on Friday.

TITLE: Michigan car owner sued after Jeep kills mechanic during oil change
SUMMARY: A Michigan man who left his car at a dealership for an oil change and tire rotation is being sued after his vehicle killed a mechanic.

TITLE: Jeopardy champion's 23-day winning streak ends after losing by $1
SUMMARY: Jeopardy champion Mattea Roach saw her 23-game streak end Friday after losing the final match by a single dollar.

TITLE: Solo climber missing for nearly a week found dead in Alaska
SUMMARY: The body of a solo climber who has been missing for nearly a week has been found at the Denali National Park in Alaska, but search teams will not be able to attempt a rescue attempt for at least another week.

TITLE: Severe weather topples wall at North Carolina facility
SUMMARY: A wall at a North Carolina distribution center was ripped apart by a severe storm on Friday, but no injuries have been reported.

TITLE: Wisconsin dog who went viral after being left tied to fire hydrant gets new home
SUMMARY: The Wisconsin Humane Society has announced that the dog who went viral this week after its owner left her tied to a fire hydrant has found a new, temporary home.

TITLE: Texas man faces upgraded murder charge after woman found dead in cardboard box
SUMMARY: A Texas man has been charged with murder after he was initially charged him with moving a dead woman’s body which he found in his apartment complex.

TITLE: Pennsylvania boy, 9, found dead in wooded area, DA says there is a person of interest
SUMMARY: A 9-year-old boy was found dead in Pennsylvania and a person of interest in the case has been confirmed by the district attorney.

TITLE: California inmates in separate prisons killed in attacks
SUMMARY: Two inmates in separate California prisons were killed this week in attacks by other inmates, officials said.

TITLE: Minnesota police body cam shows Daunte Wright's mom in tense exchange with cops: 'I will sue you'
SUMMARY: Brooklyn Center, Minnesota police released body camera video on Friday that shows an officer grabbing the phone of Daunte Wright's mother as she was recording officers performing a traffic stop on Wednesday.

TITLE: Creepy dolls washing ashore on Texas coast: ‘There’s a lot of nightmares out there’
SUMMARY: Creepy, nightmarish-looking dolls sometimes covered in barnacles that grow out of the eyes are washing up along Texas shores, according to researchers who survey the area for sea life.

TITLE: Missing Harmony Montgomery's stepmom released on $5k bail, can't speak to estranged husband
SUMMARY: A New Hampshire judge has released Kayla Montgomery, the stepmother of missing girl Harmony Montgomery, out on $5,000 cash bond, so as long as she does not contact Harmony's father and her estranged husband, Adam Montgomery.

TITLE: Chicago man robbed, shot three times in upscale Lincoln Park neighborhood
SUMMARY: A Chicago man was robbed at gunpoint at shot three times in an upscale Chicago neighborhood early Friday morning, according to authorities.

TITLE: NYC police make arrest in sledgehammer jewelry store robbery
SUMMARY: Police in New York City say they have made one arrest related to a crew of thieves that allegedly were involved in at least 18 robberies around the city.

TITLE: Arizona dad arrested after massive brawl involving sons erupts at high school, cops say
SUMMARY: Two people have been arrested, including a father of a student, in connection with a large brawl at an Arizona high school this week.

TITLE: Texas authorities find dozens of migrants in tractor-trailer broken down on side of road
SUMMARY: Dozens of migrants were found hiding in a tractor-trailer broke down on a Texas roadway Friday morning a long distance away from the southern border, authorities said.

TITLE: Goodwill find in Texas turns out to be ancient Roman bust
SUMMARY: A marble bust that a Texas woman bought for about $35 from a Goodwill store is temporarily on display at a San Antonio museum after experts determined it was a centuries-old sculpture missing from Germany since World War II.
